12.short_description: Music collaboration platform.

18.description:
WaveStack is a music collaboration platform, either for personal, group, private or public composing, with cloud storage for your projects and tools for posting and sharing your work.

With this simple approach, they open a world of possibilities for musicians, such as remote music composition and a centered repository to organize their music project.

But WaveStack is not limited to musicians. Instead, it is also focused on musician's fans. Users can interact with the song from their favorite artist, mute an instrument track and even post a cover of the song and share it over social networks.

WaveStack is based on a freemium approach. Users have 3 GB for free to store and share their music projects. With the Musician and Producer Plans, musicians get more cloud storage to work on larger and higher quality projects, as well as collaborating securely with their band members, clients or other producers. Also, they have the possibility to sell their tracks' permissions for other people to use commercially, either for covers or remixes.
